{
  "answer": "**The exact phrase \"rang-e-mai-khana\" (or close variants like \"rang e mai khana\", \"rang-e-maikhana\", etc.) does not appear in the English translation or transliteration of *Diwan-e-Ghalib* in this corpus.**\n\nI searched extensively across the English bodies (translations and transliterations) using the phrase, its parts (\"rang-e\", \"mai-khana\", \"maikhana\"), English equivalents (\"color/colour of the wine house\", \"wine house\", \"tavern\"), and combinations, limited to Ghalib's work where possible. No matches.\n\nGhalib frequently uses wine-house (*maikhana/kharabat*) and color (*rang*) imagery separately—for example, \"tavern\" appears in translations of several ghazals (e.g., chapters 21, 42, 61), and \"rang-e-\" in phrases like \"sad-rang-e-gul\" (Chapter 58) or \"rang-e-shohrat\" (Chapter 46)—but never together as requested.[^1][^2]\n\nThe *Diwan-e-Ghalib* here contains 239 ghazals; if this is from a different collection, edition, or unpublished verse, it's not covered in the Falsafa corpus.",
